# containers/SHA256SUMS
#
# SHA256 manifest of every Apptainer SIF the platform produces. Populated
# stage-by-stage:
#   Stage 02 — `_base.sif`, `hello-world.sif`
#   Stage 03 — `openfoam-esi.sif`
#   Stage 06 — `su2-v8.sif`
#   Stage 07 — `pyfr.sif`, `nekrs.sif`
#   Stage 08 — `jax-fluids.sif`, `surrogate-smoke.sif`
#   Stage 09 — `physicsnemo.sif` (digest appended when built — Phase 2)
#   Stage 11 — `precice-distribution.sif`
#   Stage 12 — `dakota.sif`
#
# Format: same as `sha256sum` output (`<sha256> <name>`).
# Signing: SIFs are signed when the non-interactive signing path is available
# (public fingerprint at SIGNING_KEY_FINGERPRINT.txt, created in Stage 02). The
# Stage 07/08 SIFs (jax-fluids, surrogate-smoke) were initially built UNSIGNED —
# `apptainer sign` could not satisfy its TTY passphrase prompt over SSH. Stage 09
# Phase 2 fixed this (ADR-012; _apptainer_sign.sh reads AERO_SIGNING_PASSPHRASE)
# and RE-SIGNED them — their SHA256 below is the new signed-artifact digest
# (signing appends a signature, changing the bytes). physicsnemo.sif is signed at
# first build. The recorded SHA256 is the bytes-level integrity check regardless.
#
# Stage 04+: the `container_sif_sha256` MLflow provenance tag is sourced
# from this file. Any run logging a SHA not present here fails the
# `provenance-completeness` CI check.

